Configure DNS Server.

Step 1

From Server Manager > Click Add role and feature > Next > Next > Next > Check DNS Server > Next > Install

Step 2

From DNS > Right Click and select DNS Manager > Right click to Server and select configure a DNS server >
Next > Next > Next > Give Zone Name(select do not allow dynamic updates) > Next > Select No, it should not 
forward querles > Next > Finish

Step 3

From DNS Manager > Reverse Lookup Zone > Right click and select New Zone > Next > Next > Next > Next >
Give Network Id(Example: 192.168.3) > Next > Finish

Step 4

From DNS Manager > Forword lookup Zone > Select Zone Name Properties > Zone Transfer > Apply > OK 
